[SN]TITLE[SN]
Leicester paint factory L & M Spray demolished after fire

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A spray paint factory in Leicester has been demolished after it was severely damaged by a large fire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Firefighters said the L & M Spray building was unsafe following the blaze which broke out in Gladstone Street at 10:20 BST on Saturday.
Huge plumes of smoke could be seen across the city during the fire - which was started accidentally.
Several streets were closed while the fire was tackled, causing delays in the city centre.
